---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "datePublished": "2026-07-13",
  "dateModified": "2026-07-13",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is a PC hardware bottleneck?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A bottleneck occurs when one component (typically CPU or GPU) limits the performance of the rest of the system. For example, a weak CPU paired with a fast GPU cannot process frames quickly enough, leaving the GPU underutilized."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<Layout
  title="PC Hardware Bottlenecks: CPU & GPU Balancing — PSUCheck"
  description="Learn about hardware bottlenecks in gaming and rendering builds. Understand how CPU/GPU performance mismatches affect frame rates and system balancing."
  schema={faqSchema}
>
  <article class="guide-article">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="guide-header">
        <div class="guide-meta">
          <span class="badge badge-safe">✓ E-E-A-T Verified</span>
          <span>Updated: July 13, 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h1>PC Bottlenecks: CPU &amp; GPU Sizing</h1>
        <p class="guide-lead">
          Achieving balanced hardware configurations ensures you get full value from your components.
          This guide analyzes system bottlenecks and matching strategies.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="guide-layout">
        <main class="guide-content" id="main-content">
          <h2>CPU Bottlenecks</h2>
          <p>
            If your CPU is running at 100% utilization while your GPU sits at 50% or 60% load during gaming,
            your CPU is the bottleneck. The processor cannot update game state, geometry, and draw calls fast enough
            for the graphics card to render.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Common signs:</strong> Stuttering, low minimum frame rates (1% lows), and no performance improvement
            when lowering resolution or graphical settings.
          </p>

          <h2>GPU Bottlenecks</h2>
          <p>
            This is the desired state for most gaming configurations. Your GPU operates at 95-99% utilization,
            while your CPU sits at comfortable levels (20% to 50%).
          </p>
          <p>
            This ensures you are maximizing your graphical fidelity and frame delivery for the money spent on your graphics card.
          </p>

          <div class="important-warning">
            <strong>💡 Allocation Strategy:</strong> Avoid buying a $999 RTX 5080 and pairing it with a cheap $99 CPU.
            Allocate roughly 35-45% of your total budget to your GPU and 15-20% to your CPU.
          </div>

          <div style="margin-top:3rem;">
            <a href="/pc-builder" class="btn btn-primary">Plan a balanced build</a>
          </div>
        </main>

        <aside class="guide-sidebar">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Calculators</h3>
            <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;font-size:0.875rem;">
              <li><a href="/psu-calculator">⚡ PSU Calculator</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pc-builder">🖥️ PC Build Cost Calculator</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Other Guides</h3>
            <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;font-size:0.875rem;">
              <li><a href="/guides/psu-sizing-guide">PSU Sizing Guide</a></li>
              <li><a href="/guides/overclocking-power-draw">Overclocking Power</a></li>
              <li><a href="/guides/pc-idle-power">PC Idle Power</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
.guide-article { padding: 4rem 0; }
.guide-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.guide-meta { display:flex; gap: 1rem; align-items:center; font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.guide-lead { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 65ch; line-height: 1.65; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
.guide-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .guide-layout { grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 8fr) minmax(0, 4fr); }
}
.guide-content h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.guide-content p, .guide-content li { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.guide-content ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.important-warning { background: var(--color-surface-raised); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-orange); padding: 1rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
.guide-sidebar { display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap: 1.5rem; }
.guide-sidebar .card { padding: 1.25rem; }
</style>
